ure from a fresh perspective. Demonstrating the salience of both race and class in shaping leisure cultures within middle-class racialised families, this is an invaluable contribution to key sociological debates around leisure, childhoods and parenting ideologies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aChild rearingzGreat Britain. 0aEast IndianszGreat BritainxSocial life and customs. 0aLeisurexSocial aspectszGreat Britain. 0aMiddle class familieszGreat Britain. 0aPlayxSocial aspectszGreat Britain. 0aRecreationxSocial aspectszGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Classes & Economic Disparity.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831111967940 cprintz978152921951740uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529219531?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529219531423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529219531/original  a978-3-11-119679-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles